Researchers from 60 countries found that 32.5% of amphibian species are at risk due to climate change and pollution.
The Cairns Frog Hospital in Australia, facing financial struggles, had to shut down after treating hundreds of sick frogs.
In Peru, tensions between rural communities and mining companies led to blockades and environmental concerns.
Additionally, the global decline of amphibians, attributed to various factors, poses a threat to ecosystems and human life.
Efforts to address these issues include conservation projects and sustainable agricultural practices to protect amphibians and their habitats.
